'''格林尼治村'''（{{lang-en|Greenwich Village}}）是[[纽约市|纽约市]][[曼哈顿|曼哈顿]]南部下西城的一个大型居住区，大部分居民为[[中产阶级|中产阶级]]家庭，但在19世纪后期和20世纪上中叶却以[[波希米亚主义|波希米亚主义]]首都和[[垮掉的一代|垮掉的一代]]诞生地著称。具有讽刺意味的是，该区最初吸引人的那些特征最终导致其走向中产阶级化和商业化<ref name="costicr">{{cite news | last =Costic | first =Robert S. | title =Is gentrification good for the poor? | work =Perspectives | publisher =American Jurist | date =2004-04-29 | url =http://www.americanjurist.net/home/index.cfm?event=displayArticle&ustory_id=141b211c-2717-4542-aa40-31a164cff7eb | accessdate =2007-12-02 | archive-date =2016-12-20 | archive-url =https://web.archive.org/web/20161220100659/http://www.americanjurist.net/home/index.cfm?event=displayArticle&ustory_id=141b211c-2717-4542-aa40-31a164cff7eb | dead-url =no }}</ref><ref name="embers">{{Citation | last =Strenberg | first =Adam | title =Embers of Gentrification | newspaper =New York Magazine | pages =5 | date =2007-11-12 | url =http://nymag.com/news/features/40648/index4.html | accessdate =2009-04-16 | archive-date =2020-05-30 | archive-url =https://web.archive.org/web/20200530150121/https://nymag.com/news/features/40648/index4.html | dead-url =no }}</ref>。

格林尼治村得名于英国伦敦的[[格林尼治|格林尼治]]。

==範圍==
格林尼治村东到[[百老汇大道|百老汇大道]]，西到[[哈德孙河|哈德孙河]]，南到[[豪斯顿街|豪斯顿街]]，北到[[14街|14街]]。周边街区为：东面是[[东村|东村]]，南面是[[紐約蘇活區|SoHo]]，北面是[[雀兒喜_(紐約)|切尔西]]。[[东村|东村]]属于[[下东城|下东城]]，与格林尼治村无关<Ref name=EV>
[http://query.nytimes.com/gst/fullpage.html?res=990CEFD6123FF932A35752C0A963958260 F.Y.I.] {{Wayback|url=http://query.nytimes.com/gst/fullpage.html?res=990CEFD6123FF932A35752C0A963958260 |date=20200610235242 }}, "When did the East Village become the East Village and stop being part of the Lower East Side?", Jesse McKinley, ''[[New_York_Times|New York Times]]'', June 1, 1995; accessed August 26, 2008.
</ref>。[[西村_(纽约市)|西村]]是格林尼治村第七大道以西的部分，但是房地产经纪人则说是第六大道以西的部分。该街区属于纽约第八选区。

